      "first_name": "Charles",
      "last_name": "Sudbury",
      "born_year": 1831,
      "died_date": "23 June 1902",
      "died_year": 1902,
      "bio": "Charles Sudbury (b.c.1831; d.23 June 1902) was the son of a framework knitter, grocer and tea-dealer in Ilkeston. His brother Francis Sudbury (1842\u20131908) was an Alderman and the first Mayor of Ilkeston (1887\u201388). Charles married Marinah Burgin and built a substantial business as a hosiery and glove manufacturer. Prior to moving to Cavendish House on Cavendish Road East, the family had lived at 5 Tattershall Drive. They had at least ten children.\n\nProperty records: NPE PF 51: Already Judges' Lodgings in 1939. Date of Lease 13 August 1887 to Henry Daubney. Freehold purchased by Nottingham City Council and Nottingham County Council on 29 September 1953 for \u00a31,200.",
