    {
      "first_name": "Florence",
      "last_name": "Sudbury",
      "born_year": 1862,
      "bio": "Florence Sudbury was a daughter of Charles and Marinah Sudbury. She married into the Hanmore family \u2014 her daughter Gladys Hanmore (b.c.1892) appears in the 1901 and 1911 census at Cavendish House as granddaughter of Charles/Marinah. Florence appears in the 1911 census as 'Hanmore Florence M', widowed, still living at Cavendish House.\n\nFlorence M Sudbury married Louis E. Hanmore (b. 29 May 1859; d. 19 September 1905), a physician who was born and practised in Newburgh, New York State. After the death of Hanmore, Florence returned to Nottingham with her daughter Gladys Wilhelmina Hanmore. Gladys subsequently married her cousin Edward Heron Sudbury.",
